The eventual deal to sell its Northern Ireland portfolio has since been the subject of claims involving fixer payments.
The finance committee has heard an allegation that five individuals were to benefit from the sale, including one politician, First Minister Peter Robinson.
He has denied the claim as "scurrilous and unfounded."
